  "text": "This can be done by having a copy of the data structure specified by Lemma 3.1 for each row of A andÃ (which we can think of as the roots of the BSTs for A's rows). This has all of the desired properties, and in fact, is the data structure Kerenidis and Prakash use to prepare arbitrary quantum states (Theorem A.1 in [CITATION_1] ). Thus, our algorithm can operate on the same input, although any data structure supporting the operations detailed in Proposition 3.2 will also suffice.",
